Start by Installing Snap, by doing sudo apt install snapd

Then install bluemail, by doing sudo snap install bluemail

You can run it, by doing snap run bluemail

Or alternatively do this to create Symlink, sudo ln -s /snap/bin/bluemail /usr/local/bin/bluemail

And add to dmenu: do, sudo nano /usr/share/applications/bluemail.desktop 
to open nano and then paste this in and save : 

[Desktop Entry]
Name=BlueMail
Exec=snap run bluemail
Type=Application
Icon=/snap/bluemail/current/meta/gui/icon.png
Categories=Network;Email;

now restart window manager or dmenu 
 

